<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-30T13:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-30T13:44:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/6: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-30T18:00:00-00:44"><hi rend="italic">August 30,
                                        1928—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>34. Department’s 27, August 29, 11 a.m. President King today issued a
                            statement to the Associated Press and copy to the Department<note n="28" xml:id="d200fn28"><hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi></note>
                            <pb facs="0361" n="251" xml:id="pg_251"/> refuting allegations in
                            Buell’s speech. Refer to enclosure 4, despatch 348, Diplomatic, March
                            13, 1926.<note n="29" xml:id="d200fn29">Enclosure not printed; despatch
                                No. 348 printed in <ref target="frus1926v02#pg_541"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1926, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 541</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>